Value.value: I don't know what we would have done without the Cathedral and Temple here to protect us!

value.0: An icon of rugged individualism, yet renowned for its ability to hunt in packs, the noble Snuffy is an animal of both mystique and power.

Perhaps the most mysterious man to ever travel through Djedet, Chin is said to come from the mythic land of Shou Lung. His motives in the city are unknown, but most in town have come to hope he's truly only there to trade.

Value.value: I am Chin. This is all you need to know.
I have nothing to tell you. Go.
The only good merchant in this town is Muhm.

value.0: A tall, strong man with a few scars, Donkor may have seen his share of battles, but he now makes a living selling freshly-brewed beer and wine.
Idogbe is an old man, his beard long and his skin leathery from the sun. No one really knows what it is he sells, but he somehow manages to turn a profit day after day.

Value.value: I do not believe I have anything you need.
Chin...they say he is from Shou Lung. Most interesting.
I do not have anything to sell to you. Perhaps you would be better off asking Muhm, he sells all kinds of simple things.

value.0: This short hin appears quite young. The precisely adjusted goggles hide his eyes, making it impossible to read his intentions and point of focus.

Detailed carvings cover the surface of this finely-crafted door. The handiwork is of high quality and no doubt came at quite an expense.

Welcome to the the stronghold of the Morninglord! If you wish to stay here, you must obey the rules that are stated here below.

- Do NOT destroy or vandalize any decoration or item you see! Those who decide to break this rule shall pay a compensation fee.

- Do NOT slay, torture, or punish any animals here. Keep in mind, that a true Lathanderan worshipper must show respect to everything that grows and provides growth.

- Do NOT let any undead creature within the city limits! These beings, or shall we say non-beings are not tolerated either by Lathander or by any of us.

- Please keep in mind to act respectfully towards everybody. If a quarrel should emerge, solve it elsewhere rather than discussing this in the middle of the town. We do not want to upset any of the locals.

- For everyone's safety, and security precautions, helmets should be un-equipped if a guard or person of higher authority asks for it. Weapons should remain in their sheaths upon entry!

- Respect the guards, and keep in mind that you will not get away with any crime! 'What goes around, will eventually come around and hit you right in the face.'


Yours Truly,
Si'neela Akuum
